(Apr 9, 2026) Task Execution and Scheduling

1. Task Execution (@Async)

Used when you don’t want to block the request.

💡 Example use cases:
1.1 Sending email after registration
1.2 Uploading images
1.3 Logging
1.4 Calling external APIs

2. Task Scheduling (@Scheduled)

Used for repeated or timed jobs

💡 Example use cases:
2.1 Clean expired JWT tokens
2.2 Delete old data
2.3 Send daily notifications
2.4 Generate reports


